# 🧪 Part 5: Compare a Grouped Aggregation

This kind of query is common in reporting.

## Query A: Uncompressed rowstore

```sql
SELECT OrderDateKey, SUM(SalesAmount) AS TotalSales
FROM dbo.FactResellerSalesXL
GROUP BY OrderDateKey
ORDER BY OrderDateKey;
GO
```

## Query B: Page-compressed rowstore

```sql
SELECT OrderDateKey, SUM(SalesAmount) AS TotalSales
FROM dbo.FactResellerSalesXL_PageCompressed
GROUP BY OrderDateKey
ORDER BY OrderDateKey;
GO
```

## Query C: Columnstore

```sql
SELECT OrderDateKey, SUM(SalesAmount) AS TotalSales
FROM dbo.FactResellerSalesXL_CCI
GROUP BY OrderDateKey
ORDER BY OrderDateKey;
GO
```

---

## ✅ Observe

Again, compare:

* logical reads
* CPU time
* elapsed time

## Questions

1. Did the ranking change compared with the previous test?
2. Which storage format seems best for analytical queries?
3. Why might grouping benefit more from columnstore than row-by-row processing?

